<section class="l-row">
  <h2>What did I learn</h2>

  <div class="separator">
    <i class="separator__icon icon-checkmark"></i>
  </div>

  <div class="l-wrap">
    <p>First of all, I liked wiriting SASS instead of pure CSS: things like mixins, functions, and nested styles could save a lot of time during implementation. Secondly, this was my first step into the world of responsive web-development. But the most important lesson this project has taught me was the importance and purpose of the Test Driven Development. I realised why writing test before you write you code is such a good practice: it forces you to think about the structure before you start coding and gives you a clear step-by-step roadmap when you do start writing some code. Apart from that, your test suit allows you to check whether all the existing features are still working when you add some new chunk of code. I really liked the approach.</p>
